## Statistics

Given two fair die $D1$ and $D2$ with the sum of eyes $S = D1 + D2$: Calculate the conditional probability $P(D1|S)$.

$$
P(D1|S) = \frac{P(S \cap D1)}{P(S)}
$$

```{r}
die_probability <- function(S){
  # Roll the second dice
  D2 <- sample(1:6,1)
  # Get the given sum
  D1 <- S - D2
}
```
